        "title": "See also"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The returned indices are not guaranteed to be sorted according to\nthe values. Furthermore, the default selection algorithm "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "introselect"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "\nis unstable, and hence the returned indices are not guaranteed\nto be the earliest/latest occurrence of the element."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "external_url": "",
                "href": "/docs/api/ops/argpartition",
                "kind": "link",
                "target": "argpartition",
                "text": "argpartition"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " works for real/complex inputs with nan values,\nsee "
              },
              {
                "external_url": "",
                "href": "/docs/api/ops/partition",
                "kind": "link",
                "target": "partition",
                "text": "partition"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " for notes on the enhanced sort order and\ndifferent selection algorithms."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Notes"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "One dimensional array:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "import flopscope as fnp"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "x = fnp.array([3, 4, 2, 1])"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "x[fnp.argpartition(x, 3)]"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array([2, 1, 3, 4]) # may vary"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "x[fnp.argpartition(x, (1, 3))]"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array([1, 2, 3, 4]) # may vary"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "x = [3, 4, 2, 1]"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "fnp.array(x)[fnp.argpartition(x, 3)]"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array([2, 1, 3, 4]) # may vary"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Multi-dimensional array:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "x = fnp.array([[3, 4, 2], [1, 3, 1]])"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "index_array = fnp.argpartition(x, kth=1, axis=-1)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "# below is the same as fnp.partition(x, kth=1)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "fnp.take_along_axis(x, index_array, axis=-1)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array([[2, 3, 4],"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "       [1, 1, 3]])"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          }
        ],
